{"lemma":"مُنْكِرِي","slug":"مُنْكِرِي","root":"ن.ك.ر","root_slug":"ن-ك-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ك-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مُنْكِر","root":"نكر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n40531"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D9%86%D9%92%D9%83%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%8A"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"denier (who denies)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"immoral behaviour, vice, wrongdoing"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of the verb أَنْكَرَ (ʔankara, “to deny”).\n\nDerived from the passive participle of the verb أَنْكَرَ (ʔankara, “to deny”)."},"ipa":["/mun.kir/","/mun.kar/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40531","headword_ar":"مُنْكَرٌ","root":"nkr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoruwfN","text_ar":"مَعْرُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) [an explanation including several significations, here following.] ―         -b2-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ignored,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unknown;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manokuwrN","text_ar":"مَنْكُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manokuwrN","text_ar":"مَنْكُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majohuwlN","text_ar":"مَجْهُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the pass. part. n. of the verb by which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anokarahu","text_ar":"اَنْكَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is explained by Kr and in the K]; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musotanokarN","text_ar":"مُسْتَنْكَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same. (L.) For the pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munokarN","text_ar":"مُنْكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nakirN","text_ar":"نَكِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Denied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disacknowledged."},{"kind":"text","text":"(See the verb.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Deemed strange, extraordinary,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"improbable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(See again the verb.)] ―         -b5-  Any action"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disapproved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disallowed, by sound intellects;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deemed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"declared, thereby, to be bad, evil, hateful, abominable, foul, unseemly, ugly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hideous;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pronounced to be so by the law because the mind deliberates respecting the regarding it as such:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and thus it is used in the Kur, ix. 113 [and other places]: (B, TA:) or anything"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pronounced to be bad, evil, hateful, abominable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foul, and forbidden, and disapproved, disliked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hated, by the law:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) a saying, or an action,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unapproved, not approved, unaccepted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not accepted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by God: (KT:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unbecoming, indecent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"indecorous."},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoruwfN","text_ar":"مَعْرُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurofN","text_ar":"عُرْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munokarN","text_ar":"مُنْكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nukorN","text_ar":"نُكْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nukurN","text_ar":"نُكُرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nakoraA='u","text_ar":"نَكْرَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb K) are all syn., (S, A, Msb, K,) [and are used as epithets in which the quality of a subst. predominates,] signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bad, an evil, a hateful, an abominable, a foul, an unseemly, an ugly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hideous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a formidable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2851},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"action"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saying"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (Msb:) [in this sense, its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munokaraAtN","text_ar":"مُنْكَرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaAkiyru","text_ar":"مَنَاكِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as will be seen below:] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nukorN","text_ar":"نُكْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurofN","text_ar":"عُرْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoruwfN","text_ar":"مَعْرُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhimu","text_ar":"فِيهِمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@lomaEoruwfu waA@lomunokaru","text_ar":"ا@لْمَعْرُوفُ وَا@لْمُنْكَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEurofu wAln~ukoru","text_ar":"العُرْفُ والنُّكْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In them are good and evil qualities."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo yarokabuwna A@lomunokaraAti","text_ar":"هُمْ يَرْكَبُونَ ا@لْمُنْكَرَاتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmanaAkiyra","text_ar":"المَنَاكِيرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They commit bad, evil, abominable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foul, actions."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (A.) And it is said in the Kur, [xviii. 73,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqado jiy^ota $ayoy^FA nukorFA","text_ar":"لَقَدْ جِيْتَ شَيْيًا نُكْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily thou hast done a bad, an evil, an abominable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a foul, thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The name of one of two angels, the other of whom is named"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nakiyrN","text_ar":"نَكِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) who are the two triers of [the dead in] the graves. (ISd, K.)       -A3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nakirN","text_ar":"نَكِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["K","B","TA","KT","S","A","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}